CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F405A1778343067
OL,3,CPolanski declares two-party politics
OL,4,C'dead' after Green mayor elected in
OL,5,CHackney
OL,7,FMs Garbett won with 35,720 votes to
OL,8,Fformer Labour mayor Caroline Woodley's
OL,9,F26,685.
OL,11,FGreen Party leader Mr Polanski called
OL,12,Fit "a historic victory".
OL,14,FHe added: "This is the first time the
OL,15,FGreen Party has ever won a directly-
OL,16,Felected mayor.
OL,18,F"Two-party politics is not just dying,
OL,19,Fit is dead and it is buried.
OL,26,@tD@DOUtD@WO]vD@KOUzD@AOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/6
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,406,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F405A1778343067
OL,3,CPolanski declares two-party politics
OL,4,C'dead' after Green mayor elected in
OL,5,CHackney
OL,7,F"And actually, whether it's here that
OL,8,FLabour have been rejected, or whether
OL,9,Fwe're seeing around the country, it's
OL,10,Fvery clear that the new politics is
OL,11,Fthe Green Party versus Reform."
OL,13,FAsked for a message to the Reform UK
OL,14,Fleader, he said: "Nigel Farage, I
OL,15,Fdon't have a lot to say to him."
OL,17,FHe called for Prime Minister Sir Keir
OL,18,FStarmer to stand down, saying the
OL,19,Fresults from local elections so far
OL,20,Fshow that the country has rejected him.
OL,26,@oD@AOUsD@_O]vD@ROUwD@`O]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/6
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,406,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F405A1778343067
OL,3,CPolanski declares two-party politics
OL,4,C'dead' after Green mayor elected in
OL,5,CHackney
OL,7,F"My message to Keir Starmer is it's
OL,8,Ftime to go," he said
OL,10,F"The country has clearly rejected you.
OL,11,FI think he'd been rejected before
OL,12,Fthese elections even started.
OL,14,F"We had 14 years of Conservative
OL,15,Fausterity
OL,17,F"Keir Starmer was voted in on a
OL,18,Fpromise of change and, actually, what
OL,19,Fwe've seen is very little change, and
OL,20,Fin many ways things have got worse."
OL,26,@oD@AOUpD@LO]rD@AOUvD@AOUyD@AOU|D@dO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/6
